Quote: On the gentler slopes subject to soil movement, widely spaced planting of trees, spot planting as it is called, will furnish tree roots which will anchor the soil without adversely affecting the pasture.. Spot planting, while primarily concerned with stabilising the soil of hill country pastures ...
